alog Republic]]).}}\n|Pro-Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio\n|Manila\n|-\n|[[Apolonio Samson]][[File:General Apolonio Samson.jpg|thumb|General Apolonio Samson]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"2\"|\n*Katipunan General<ref>[http://tagaloglang.com/Famous-Filipinos/Patriots/talambuhay-ni-apolonio-samson.html Talambuhay ni Apolonio Samson] published by Tagaloglang.com; accessed 2013-11-03.</ref>\n*One of the leaders present in the [[Cry of Pugad Lawin]]\n*Head of Katipunan in Caloocan<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Zaide|first=Gregorio|date=1990|title=Cry of balintawak|url=|journal=Documentary Sources of Philippine History|volume=8|pages=307\u2013309|via=}}</ref>\n|\n*Katipunan in Caloocan\n*Magdiwang\n|Caloocan , Manila\n|-\n|[[Teodoro Sandiko]][[File:General Teodoro Sandiko (Sandico) (1860-1939).tif|thumb|General Teodoro Sandiko (Sandico)]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Also noted as Teodoro Sandico\n*Brigadier General\n|\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Katipunan\n|Pandacan, Manila\n|-\n|[[Benito Santa Ana]]\n|\n|{{sort|1|Brigadier General}}\n|?\n|?\n|-\n|[[Julian Santos]]\n|\n|{{sort|1|General, Field Commander}}<ref name=\"IV2011\">{{cite book|author=Himerio Jose Dela Llana Garcia IV|title=Brigands in the Eyes of the Law- section: US vs. Julian Santos, et al. (2Phil 669)-&#91;CFI-Rizal&#93;, No. 1338. November 7, 1903.&#93;|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9CFqDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT5|date=14 June 2011|publisher=Flipside Digital Content Company Inc.|isbn=978-971-9922-24-7}}</ref>\n|Katipunan, First Philippine Republic, Tagalog Republic\n|Rizal (Morong), Bulacan\n|-\n|[[Luciano San Miguel]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General<ref>{{cite book|last=Dept|first=United States. War|title=Annual Reports of the Secretary of War|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cAoSAAAAYAAJ|year=1904|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=cAoSAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA41&dq=%22Luciano+San+Miguel%22 41]}}</ref>\n*Commander of the rebel lines in San Francisco de Malabon\n*\u201