ogistics of the Katipuneros and later joined the American Revolution in Cavite.}}</ref>\n*He used the pen name \u201cLanggam\u201d (Ant) and was the founder of Pilar Lodge No. 15 of the Free Masonry of the Philippines \n|\n*Katipunan\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Tagalog Republic as headed by General Miguel Malvar\n|[[Imus]], Cavite\n|-\n|[[Arsenio Climaco]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General\n|?\n|?\n|-\n|[[Juan Climaco]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|Brigadier General\n|Neutral\n|Cebu\n|-\n|[[Venancio Concepcion]]\n|\n|{{sort|2|Major General}}\n|Pro-Antonio Luna\n|[[Iloilo]]\n|-\n|[[Berixio Consola]][[File:General Berixio Consola.tif|thumb|General Berixio Consola]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*General\n*Insurgent general<ref>{{cite book|title=United States Congressional Serial Set|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HwtHAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA664|year=1902|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|page=292}}</ref>\n|\n*Tagalog Republic of General Miguel Malvar\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Revolutionary Government of the Philippines\n*Katipunan\n|\n*Military campaigns during Filipino-American War in Batalan Bato and Lobo in [[Batangas]]\n|-\n|[[Esteban Contreras]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Brigadier General<ref name=Dacudao>{{cite document | author = Dr. Jose Maria Eduardo P. Dacudao | title = Forget Not How Visayan Patriots Won Our Freedom | publisher = Ilonggo Sa America (I.S.A) | date = 20 November 2011| page = 1 | <!--accessdate = 2020-04-05--> }}</ref>\n*May 4, 1898- lead an attack to Spanish military in Capiz\n*December 1898 defeated Spanish troops in the town of Pila\n|\n*Federated States of Visayas\n*First Philippine Republic\n*Katipunan in the Visayas\n*Revolutionary leader in Panay\n|[[Capiz]],[[Panay]]\n|-\n|[[Gregorio Coronel]]\n|\n|{{sort|1|Brigadier General}}\n|Pro-Andr\u00e9s Bonifacio\n|?\n|-\n|[[Angel Corteza]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"1\"|\n*Commanding General of the Southern Zone <ref name=Dacudao/>- appointed during revolutionary assembly to