v.ph/AB01/1899/aug/24/jpg/7.jpg|format=JPG |language=Spanish, Filipino |work=Ang Bayang Kahapis-hapis |location=San Francisco de Malabon, Cavite |access-date=2019-03-06 }}\n</ref>\n}}\n|\n*Katipunan-Magdiwang\n*First Philippine Republic\n|Cavite\n|-\n|[[Artemio Ricarte]][[File:General Artemio Ricarte.tif|thumb|General Artemio Ricarte]]\n|\n|{{sort|3|Lieutenant General<ref>{{Harvnb| Alvarez|1992|p=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3q\u2013krDckHwC&pg=PA42 42]}}</ref> (Captain General from 1897 to 1898)<ref>{{Harvnb|Zaide|Zaide|1999|p=247}}.</ref>}}\n|Magdiwang (Mapagtiis)\n|Cavite (Batac, Ilocos Norte)\n|-\n|[[Ruperto Rios]]\n|\n|data-sort-value=\"6\"|\n*Also noted as Ruperto Reus\n*Viceroy-General<ref>{{cite news|url=http://opinion.inquirer.net/98377/king-of-the-philippines|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021123104/https://opinion.inquirer.net/98377/king-of-the-philippines|archivedate=2016-10-21|title=King of the Philippines|newspaper=Philippine Daily Inquirer|date=October 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Google books| ML9MAAAAYAAJ|1904 Annual Report of the Secretary of War: Volume 7 United States War Dept|page=38}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Hurley|first=Vic|title=Jungle Patrol, the Story of the Philippine Constabulary (1901-1936)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fAuBedlSboIC|year=2011|publisher=Cerberus Books|isbn=978-0-9834756-2-0|pages=[https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=fAuBedlSboIC&pg=PA125&dq=%22riso%22 125\u2013127], [https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=fAuBedlSboIC&pg=PA=156&&dq=%22riso%22 156]}}</ref>\n*\"Colorum\" <ref>1975, Renato Constantino, The Philippines: A Past Revisited, page 350: \"The colorums believed that one day he would rule the Philippines. When this came to pass, the property of all those who were not colorums would be confiscated and apportioned among the members. Like other colorums elsewhere, the Surigao group believed themselves invulnerable to the enemy's bullets.\"<!--taken from information at {{Wiktionary|colorum}}--></r